################################################################################
# Atom-atom electronic relaxation in a 0-D thermal reservoir
#
# Pure atomic oxygen in a box: translation starts hot (30000 K) while the
# electronic mode starts cold (all atoms in the ground state, T_elec = 100 K).
# Atomic O has zero rotational and vibrational degrees of freedom, so the
# electronic mode can only relax through atom-atom collisions. Over the run
# the electronic states populate toward a Boltzmann distribution and the
# translational and electronic temperatures approach a common value.
#
# Note:
#  - The "comm/sort" option to the "global" command is used to match MPI runs.
#  - The "twopass" option is used to match Kokkos runs.
# The "comm/sort" and "twopass" options should not be used for production runs.
################################################################################

